rs experiments are not\nconsistent with the principle of relativity; why the traditionally-argued\ninvariance of information velocity contradicts Maxwell equations; and why the\nsuperluminal light pulse propagation claimed in Wang-Kuzmich-Dogariu\nexperiments voilates Einstein causality.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Jun 2013 06:00:52 GMT"},{"version":"v10","created":"Wed, 28 Dec 2016 19:03:47 GMT"},{"version":"v11","created":"Thu, 16 Feb 2017 19:18:37 GMT"},{"version":"v12","created":"Mon, 31 Jul 2017 05:54:54 GMT"},{"version":"v13","created":"Mon, 30 Sep 2019 19:01:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Aug 2014 17:46:34 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 19 Jan 2015 16:25:33 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 11 May 2015 11:52:05 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 31 Aug 2015 13:54:11 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Mon, 4 Apr 2016 16:52:06 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Mon, 2 May 2016 07:20:29 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Tue, 10 May 2016 17:39:17 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Wed, 14 Sep 2016 06:09:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-15"}
